                </div>

                <p>The<span class="font-weight-700"> new Norton V4 </span>is set to succeed the acclaimed V4SV, and early glimpses via spy shots suggest a more aggressive, modern, and globally competitive design. The V4SV already set a high bar with its exquisite craftsmanship—featuring an exposed, mirror-polished aluminium tube frame, premium components, and an unmistakable British flair. The upcoming model, however, looks ready to shed some of that retro-inspired styling for a truly contemporary superbike silhouette, one that can go toe-to-toe with the world’s best on the showroom floor and on the racetrack.</p>
                <p>Sources indicate that Norton has listened to the market, focusing on compliance, performance, and cutting-edge technology. The shift in design philosophy hints at improved aerodynamics, better mass centralisation, and an overall package engineered for peak performance. This new machine represents the true global ambition of the TVS-backed Norton, designed to meet modern emission standards (like Euro 5+) and finally conquer markets beyond the UK.</p>
